              "id": "p1",
              "name": "chatInput",
              "value": "={{ 'Analyze the ' + $('SET Normalize Input').item.json.channel_name + ' presence of this brand.\\n\\nHandle: ' + $('SET Normalize Input').item.json.channel_handle + '\\nURL: ' + $('SET Normalize Input').item.json.channel_url + '\\n\\nScraped content:\\n---\\n' + ($json.data || $json.content || $json.text || JSON.stringify($json)).slice(0, 5000) + '\\n---\\n\\nReturn ONLY valid JSON (no markdown, no backticks):\\n{\\n  \"tone\": \"2-3 sentence description of the channel tone\",\\n  \"formality\": \"formal|professional|casual|mixed\",\\n  \"voice_rules\": {\\n    \"do\": [\"rule 1\", \"rule 2\", \"rule 3\"],\\n    \"dont\": [\"rule 1\", \"rule 2\", \"rule 3\"]\\n  },\\n  \"top_posts\": [\\n    { \"text\": \"post excerpt or description (max 80 chars)\", \"why_it_works\": \"reason (max 60 chars)\" }\\n  ],\\n  \"content_patterns\": [\"pattern 1\", \"pattern 2\", \"pattern 3\"],\\n  \"posting_style\": \"1 sentence about posting cadence and format\"\\n}\\n\\nLimits: voice_rules max 5 each, top_posts max 3, content_patterns max 4. If content is limited return best estimate.' }}",
